<subSubSection pageId="51" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="51.[128,654,694,1449]" pageId="51" pageNumber="51">
COMMENTS: In his report on Baron’s 1894 expedition to 
<collectingCountry box="[306,363,989,1010]" name="Peru" pageId="51" pageNumber="51">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Salvin, O." box="[383,545,988,1010]" pageId="51" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 22" refId="ref101454" refString="Salvin, O. 1895. On birds collected in Peru by Mr. O. T. Baron. Novitates Zoologicae 2: 1 - 22, pls. I, II." type="journal article" year="1895">Salvin (1895)</bibRefCitation>
did not designate types but noted (
<bibRefCitation author="Salvin, O." box="[462,643,1017,1040]" pageId="51" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 22" refId="ref101454" refString="Salvin, O. 1895. On birds collected in Peru by Mr. O. T. Baron. Novitates Zoologicae 2: 1 - 22, pls. I, II." type="journal article" year="1895">Salvin, 1895: 1</bibRefCitation>
) that the collection was partly in the Rothschild Collection (now in AMNH) and partly in the Salvin and Godman Collection (now in BMNH). Of 
<emphasis box="[278,383,1135,1156]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="51">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Salvin" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[278,379,1135,1156]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Atlapetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufigenis">rufigenis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
there are 
<specimenCount box="[498,653,1134,1156]" pageId="51" pageNumber="51" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">four syntypes</specimenCount>
in BMNH (
<bibRefCitation author="Warren, R. L. M. &amp; C. J. O. Harrison" box="[264,646,1164,1186]" pageId="51" pageNumber="51" refId="ref103142" refString="Warren, R. L. M., and C. J. O. Harrison. 1971. Type-specimens of birds in the British Museum (Natural History). Volume 2. Passerines. London: Trustees of the British Museum (Natural History), 628 pp." type="book" year="1971">Warren and Harrison, 1971: 478</bibRefCitation>
) in addition to the three in AMNH. While all three AMNH specimens are 
<typeStatus box="[547,650,1223,1244]" pageId="51" pageNumber="51">syntypes</typeStatus>
, AMNH 519569 and 519572 were marked ‘‘Co-type’’ by Salvin, even though they were not listed by Hartert in any of his lists of types in the Rothschild Collection and did not bear Rothschild type labels. Dickinson (2003: 801) has accorded full species status to both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="rufigenis (Salvin" authorityYear="1895" box="[191,352,1427,1448]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Atlapetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="rufigenis" subSpecies="rufigenis">
<emphasis box="[191,352,1427,1448]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="51">A. r. rufigenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[413,552,1426,1449]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Atlapetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="forbesi">
<emphasis box="[413,552,1426,1449]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="51">A. r. forbesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
